@startuml esc_aeb_input_to_vsm_intervention_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title ESC AEB Input To VSM Intervention Signal Flow\n(ESC + AEB + speed context -> VSM control and intervention publish)

participant "ESC / AEB /\nvehicle speed inputs" as VsmCtx #F4F7FB
participant "VSM\nstability manager owner" as VSM #E8F7E8
participant "VSM state bus" as VsmBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / brake users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Stability Inputs ==

VsmCtx -> VSM : escCtrlState / escIntervention\naebArmed / stopReq / decelProfile / domainHealth\nvehicleSpeed
VSM -> VSM : if ESC stale then\nesc state/intervention = 0
VSM -> VSM : if AEB stale then\narmed = 0 / stopReq = 0 / decelProfile = 0 / domainHealth = 1
VSM -> VSM : ctrlState escalates when stale or AEB armed\nand reaches 3 when domainHealth <= 0
VSM -> VSM : intervention = ESC intervention\nraised to 20/35/50/60 by AEB profile / stopReq
note right of VSM
Representative gating inputs
- escCtrlState / escIntervention
- aebArmed / stopReq / decelProfile
- aebDomainHealth
- vehicleSpeed
end note

== VSM Publish ==

VSM -> VsmBus : frmVsmStateMsg\nVsmCtrlState / VsmAlertLevel / VsmIntervention
note right of VSM
Representative outputs
- VsmCtrlState
- VsmAlertLevel
- VsmIntervention
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

VsmBus -> Obs : stability-intervention readback /\nbrake-assist observers

note over VsmCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. ESC, AEB, and speed context reach VSM
2. VSM derives control state and effective intervention level
3. VSM publishes stability state and intervention magnitude
4. Brake-assist observers consume the final VSM posture
end note

@enduml
